                <h2 class="subheading">Pre-Transfer Checklist</h2>
                <ul>
                    <li>Ensure the vehicle has no pending challans (check via eChallan portal)</li>
                    <li>Clear loan hypothecation if active</li>
                    <li>Verify insurance and PUC validity</li>
                    <li>Make a notarized sale agreement</li>
                    <li>Scan and keep digital copies ready</li>
                </ul>

                <div class="div-line"></div>
                <h2 class="subheading">Step-by-Step Guide to Online RC Transfer (Same State)</h2>

                <h3 class="subheading">Step 1: Visit the Parivahan Portal</h3>
                <p>Go to <a href="https://parivahan.gov.in" class="for-link">https://parivahan.gov.in</a> and select "Vehicle Related Services."</p>

                <h3 class="subheading">Step 2: Choose State and RTO</h3>
                <p>Select your respective state and RTO office.</p>

                <h3 class="subheading">Step 3: Select "Transfer of Ownership"</h3>
                <p>Enter the vehicle registration number and chassis number (last 5 digits).</p>

                <h3 class="subheading">Step 4: Fill Buyer and Seller Details</h3>
                <p>Include names, addresses, contact details, and sale date.</p>

                <h3 class="subheading">Step 5: Upload Documents</h3>
                <p>Submit scanned copies of RC, Form 29 & 30, ID proofs, insurance, and PUC.</p>

                <h3 class="subheading">Step 6: Pay Online Fee</h3>
                <p>Fees can be paid via UPI, cards, or internet banking.</p>

                <h3 class="subheading">Step 7: Book RTO Appointment (if required)</h3>
                <p>Some RTOs may ask for physical verification.</p>

                <h3 class="subheading">Step 8: Submit Acknowledgment Receipt</h3>
                <p>Keep a digital/printed copy of your application for reference.</p>

                <div class="div-line"></div>
                <h2 class="subheading">Online RC Transfer for Inter-State Vehicle</h2>
                <h3 class="subheading">Additional Steps:</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Apply for NOC from original RTO using Form 28</li>
                    <li>Submit Form 27 (re-registration) and pay applicable road tax</li>
                    <li>Transfer RC after receiving NOC and re-registration</li>
                </ul>
                <p><span class="font-weight-700">Note:</span> New RC will have the updated RTO code of the buyer's state.</p>

